---
const bibtex = `@software{synthbench2026,
  title   = {SynthBench: Open Benchmark for Synthetic Survey Respondents},
  author  = {DataViking-Tech},
  year    = {2026},
  url     = {https://github.com/DataViking-Tech/synthbench},
  version = {0.1.0}
}`;
---

<div class="bg-surface py-24 sm:py-32 dark:bg-surface-dark" id="about">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl lg:text-center">
      <h2 class="text-base/7 font-semibold text-primary dark:text-primary-light">Open Benchmark</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-pretty text-text sm:text-5xl lg:text-balance dark:text-text-dark">About SynthBench</p>
      <p class="mt-6 text-lg/8 text-muted">
        SynthBench is an open benchmark that measures how well large language models
        replicate human survey response distributions. It compares synthetic respondent
        outputs against real survey data across multiple datasets and demographics.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Methodology + Metrics: 2x2 grid with icons -->
    <div class="mx-auto mt-16 max-w-2xl sm:mt-20 lg:mt-24 lg:max-w-4xl">
      <dl class="grid max-w-xl grid-cols-1 gap-x-8 gap-y-10 lg:max-w-none lg:grid-cols-2 lg:gap-y-16">
        <div class="relative pl-16">
          <dt class="text-base/7 font-semibold text-text dark:text-text-dark">
            <div class="absolute top-0 left-0 flex size-10 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-primary dark:bg-primary-light">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" aria-hidden="true" class="size-6 text-white">
                <path d="M9.75 3.104v5.714a2.25 2.25 0 0 1-.659 1.591L5 14.5M9.75 3.104c-.251.023-.501.05-.75.082m.75-.082a24.3 24.3 0 0 1 4.5 0m0 0v5.714c0 .597.237 1.17.659 1.591L19.8 15.3M14.25 3.104c.251.023.501.05.75.082M19.8 15.3l-1.57.393A9.065 9.065 0 0 1 12 15a9.065 9.065 0 0 0-6.23.693L5 14.5m14.8.8 1.402 1.402c1.232 1.232.65 3.318-1.067 3.611A48.309 48.309 0 0 1 12 21c-2.773 0-5.491-.235-8.135-.687-1.718-.293-2.3-2.379-1.067-3.61L5 14.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" />
              </svg>
            </div>
            Methodology
          </dt>
          <dd class="mt-2 text-base/7 text-muted">
            Models generate synthetic survey responses matching real demographic profiles.
            We measure quality using the Survey Parity Score (SPS), Jensen-Shannon Divergence
            (JSD), and Kendall's Tau rank correlation. Confidence intervals are computed via
            bootstrap resampling.
          </dd>
        </div>
        <div class="relative pl-16">
          <dt class="text-base/7 font-semibold text-text dark:text-text-dark">
            <div class="absolute top-0 left-0 flex size-10 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-primary dark:bg-primary-light">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" aria-hidden="true" class="size-6 text-white">
                <path d="M3 13.125C3 12.504 3.504 12 4.125 12h2.25c.621 0 1.125.504 1.125 1.125v6.75C7.5 20.496 6.996 21 6.375 21h-2.25A1.125 1.125 0 0 1 3 19.875v-6.75ZM9.75 8.625c0-.621.504-1.125 1.125-1.125h2.25c.621 0 1.125.504 1.125 1.125v11.25c0 .621-.504 1.125-1.125 1.125h-2.25a1.125 1.125 0 0 1-1.125-1.125V8.625ZM16.5 4.125c0-.621.504-1.125 1.125-1.125h2.25C20.496 3 21 3.504 21 4.125v15.75c0 .621-.504 1.125-1.125 1.125h-2.25a1.125 1.125 0 0 1-1.125-1.125V4.125Z" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" />
              </svg>
            </div>
            SPS (Survey Parity Score)
          </dt>
          <dd class="mt-2 text-base/7 text-muted">
            Primary metric. 1.0 = perfect match to human distributions. Combines distribution
            similarity and rank preservation into a single 0-1 score.
          </dd>
        </div>
        <div class="relative pl-16">
          <dt class="text-base/7 font-semibold text-text dark:text-text-dark">
            <div class="absolute top-0 left-0 flex size-10 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-primary dark:bg-primary-light">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" aria-hidden="true" class="size-6 text-white">
                <path d="M7.5 14.25v2.25m3-4.5v4.5m3-6.75v6.75m3-9v9M6 20.25h12A2.25 2.25 0 0 0 20.25 18V6A2.25 2.25 0 0 0 18 3.75H6A2.25 2.25 0 0 0 3.75 6v12A2.25 2.25 0 0 0 6 20.25Z" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" />
              </svg>
            </div>
            JSD (Jensen-Shannon Divergence)
          </dt>
          <dd class="mt-2 text-base/7 text-muted">
            Measures distributional distance between synthetic and human responses. Lower is
            better. 0 = identical distributions.
          </dd>
        </div>
        <div class="relative pl-16">
          <dt class="text-base/7 font-semibold text-text dark:text-text-dark">
            <div class="absolute top-0 left-0 flex size-10 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-primary dark:bg-primary-light">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" aria-hidden="true" class="size-6 text-white">
                <path d="M3 7.5 7.5 3m0 0L12 7.5M7.5 3v13.5m13.5 0L16.5 21m0 0L12 16.5m4.5 4.5V7.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" />
              </svg>
            </div>
            Tau (Kendall's Rank Correlation)
          </dt>
          <dd class="mt-2 text-base/7 text-muted">
            Measures rank-order agreement between synthetic and human response distributions.
            Higher is better. 1.0 = perfect rank agreement.
          </dd>
        </div>
      </dl>
    </div>

    <!-- Datasets: 3-column simple grid -->
    <div class="mx-auto mt-16 max-w-7xl sm:mt-20 lg:mt-24">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl lg:mx-0">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-text dark:text-text-dark">Datasets</h3>
      </div>
      <dl class="mx-auto mt-10 grid max-w-2xl grid-cols-1 gap-x-8 gap-y-16 text-base/7 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:mx-0 lg:max-w-none lg:grid-cols-3">
        <div>
          <dt class="font-semibold text-text dark:text-text-dark">SubPOP</dt>
          <dd class="mt-1 text-muted">Subset of Pew Opinion Polls. US demographic focus with political and social attitudes.</dd>
        </div>
        <div>
          <dt class="font-semibold text-text dark:text-text-dark">OpinionsQA</dt>
          <dd class="mt-1 text-muted">Cross-sectional opinion survey covering economic, social, and political topics.</dd>
        </div>
        <div>
          <dt class="font-semibold text-text dark:text-text-dark">GlobalQA</dt>
          <dd class="mt-1 text-muted">Global attitudes survey with cross-cultural demographic representation.</dd>
        </div>
      </dl>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- Citation section -->
<section class="bg-surface py-16 dark:bg-surface-dark" id="citation">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl lg:mx-0">
      <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-text dark:text-text-dark">Citation</h3>
      <p class="mt-4 text-base/7 text-muted">
        If you use SynthBench in your research, please cite:
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="relative mt-8 max-w-2xl">
      <pre class="rounded-lg border border-muted/20 bg-surface p-6 text-sm/6 font-mono text-text overflow-x-auto dark:bg-surface-dark dark:text-text-dark">{bibtex}</pre>
      <button
        type="button"
        class="absolute top-3 right-3 rounded-md p-2 text-muted hover:text-text dark:hover:text-text-dark"
        id="copy-bibtex"
        aria-label="Copy BibTeX"
        data-bibtex={bibtex}
      >
        <svg class="size-5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor" aria-hidden="true">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M15.666 3.888A2.25 2.25 0 0013.5 2.25h-3c-1.03 0-1.9.693-2.166 1.638m7.332 0c.055.194.084.4.084.612v0a.75.75 0 01-.75.75H9.75a.75.75 0 01-.75-.75v0c0-.212.03-.418.084-.612m7.332 0c.646.049 1.288.11 1.927.184 1.1.128 1.907 1.077 1.907 2.185V19.5a2.25 2.25 0 01-2.25 2.25H6.75A2.25 2.25 0 014.5 19.5V6.257c0-1.108.806-2.057 1.907-2.185a48.208 48.208 0 011.927-.184" />
        </svg>
      </button>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<script>
  const btn = document.getElementById("copy-bibtex");
  if (btn) {
    btn.addEventListener("click", () => {
      const text = btn.dataset.bibtex ?? "";
      navigator.clipboard.writeText(text).then(() => {
        btn.setAttribute("aria-label", "Copied!");
        setTimeout(() => btn.setAttribute("aria-label", "Copy BibTeX"), 2000);
      });
    });
  }
</script>
